aa(lp24
VTo produce these animations, an animator at a studio has to anticipate
p25
aVwhat's going to happen in the actual game,
p26
aVand then has to animate that particular sequence.
p27
aVSo, he or she sits down, animates it, and tries to anticipate what's going to happen,
p28
aVand then these particular animations are just played back
p29
aVat appropriate times in the computer game.
p30
aVNow, the result of that is that you can't have real interactivity.
p31
aVAll you have is animations that are played back
p32
aVat more or less the appropriate times.
p33
aVIt also means that games aren't really going to be as surprising as they could be,
p34
aVbecause you only get out of it, at least in terms of the character,
p35
aVwhat you actually put into it.
p36
aVThere's no real emergence there.
