aVThe tricky bit is now to put an AI controller in it
p63
aVthat actually makes it work.
p64
aVAnd for that, we use the neural network, which we based on
p65
aVthat part of the nervous system that we have in our spine
p66
aVthat controls walking in humans.
p67
aVIt's called the central pattern generator.
p68
aVSo, we simulated that as well, and then the really tricky bit
p69
aVis to teach that network how to walk.
p70
aVFor that we used artificial evolution \u2014 genetic algorithms.
p71
aa(lp72
VWe heard about those already yesterday,
p73
aVand I suppose that most of you are familiar with that already.
p74
aVBut, just briefly, the concept is that
p75
aVyou create a large number of different individuals \u2014
p76
aVneural networks, in this case \u2014
p77
aVall of which are random at the beginning.
p78
aVYou hook these up \u2014 in this case, to the virtual muscles
p79
aVof that two-legged creature here \u2014
p80
aVand hope that it does something interesting.
p81
